 That is, find the entries of 
\begin_inset Formula $C$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $d$
\end_inset

 (in terms of 
\begin_inset Formula $\vec{a}_{1},\vec{a}_{2},\vec{b}_{1},\vec{b}_{2}$
\end_inset

